"Elimination or replacement: High temperature: Working in covered areas; avoid working in extremely hot environments. Low temperature: Avoid working in extremely cold environments.
Engineering controls: High temperature: 
 Automation and mechanization of tasks;
 Ventilation and air conditioning, installing exhaust fans;
 Insulating hot surfaces; 
 Shielding.
 Low temperature: Thermal insulation.
Administrative and PPE: High temperature: 
 Rotation of work; Shorten exposure duration and use frequent rest breaks;
 Intervals for fluid intake avoiding dehydration at elevated temperatures;
 Train workers in recognition of symptoms of heat exposure; 
 Wear sunscreens, caps or hats;
 Wear loose clothing that will allow sweat evaporation. 

Low temperature: 
 Intervals for the ingestion of hot drinks avoiding the consequences of low temperatures;
 Stay dry; 
 Keep active;
 Rotation of work;
 Train workers in recognition of symptoms of low temperature exposure;
 Dress in layers of warm clothing including water proof and wind resistant wear.

