"The following statements are true regarding safety procedures when operating machinery:
" "1) Before starting any machine or equipment, make sure it is safe to do so;
" "2) Make sure that the operator of any machine or equipment has access to the shutdown;
" "3) Do not enter machines or equipment while on or in motion;
" "4) Discard machines or equipment that may not be safe;
" "5) All of the above
"

"The danger of overturning on farms that use tractors can result in workers' crushing and drowning. What options are true to mitigate this risk?
" "1) Install security cabin (ROPS) and seat belts to prevent the worker from being thrown out and crushed by machinery;
" "2) Install hydraulic jack for the worker to lift the tractor in case of overturning;
" "3) Stay away from slopes and gaps.
"

"All workers should receive education and training on the health and safety risks of sodium metabisulfite. The following statements are true regarding safety procedures when using this and other highly toxic compounds:
" "1) Replace toxic or lethal products;
" "2) Use in a poorly ventilated environment;
" "3) Wear protective clothing and respirator masks;
" "4) Wash hands thoroughly after exposure to sodium metabisulphite and at the end of work shift.
"

"Employers should select the most viable, effective and permanent controls according to a hierarchy. To mitigate risks, the correct hierarchical sequence of risk control is:
" "1) Safe work practices and administrative controls;
" "2) Solutions including elimination or replacement;
" "3) Protective personal equipment.
"

"Manual vaccination of fish may lead to needlestick injuries and infections. Indicate the best alternative for eliminating the risk of perforation during the vaccination of fish in aquaculture:
" "1) Install automatic vaccination equipment;
" "2) Use corrugated table to immobilize the fish in the wavy groove;
" "3) Wear anti-cutting gloves.
"

"Constant exposure to noise emitted by the boat engine, oyster washing machines and high pressure can lead to hearing damage and deafness. To mitigate risks, the correct hierarchical sequence of risk control is:
" "1) Build barriers that prevent noise from reaching the worker;
" "2) Wear hearing protection;
" "3) Replacement for less noise equipment.
"

"The pond aerator has stopped working and this can affect all production. What you should do?
